                            <comment id="245187" author="mdiep" created="Wed, 3 Apr 2019 14:14:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on b2_12: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0fb97ed2-552d-11e9-9720-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/0fb97ed2-552d-11e9-9720-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
what&apos;s the next step on this failure?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="238815" author="adilger" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2018 01:38:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think we will be patching 2.11, ao it probably is not worthwhile. This test should just be added to the EXCEPT list when running 2.11 interop. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="238790" author="tappro" created="Tue, 18 Dec 2018 19:36:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, this is not a bug, should I make a patch for pre-2.12 clients to don&apos;t fail?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="238721" author="adilger" created="Mon, 17 Dec 2018 23:44:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is a non-bug, as we changed the MDS code to silently convert the too-large DoM component size to be limited by the &lt;tt&gt;lod.&amp;#42;.dom_stripesize&lt;/tt&gt; limit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Assigning to Mike to verify, but I think this can be closed as &quot;Not a bug&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
